
<p class="card-text">
	<sup class="verse-number">3</sup> Speak ye unto all the congregation of Israel, saying,
	In the tenth [day] of this month they shall take to them every man a lamb,
	according to the house of [their] fathers, a lamb for an house:
	
	<sup class="verse-number">4</sup> And if the household be too little for the lamb,
	let him and his neighbour next unto his house take [it] according to the number of the souls;
	every man according to his eating shall make your count for the lamb.
	
	<sup class="verse-number">5</sup> Your lamb shall be without blemish,
	a male of the first year: ye shall take [it] out from the sheep, or from the goats:
	<sup class="verse-number">6</sup> And ye shall keep it up until the fourteenth day of the same month:
	and the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel shall kill it in the evening.
</p>

<p class="card-text">
	<sup class="verse-number">7</sup> And they shall take of the blood, 
	and strike [it] on the two side posts <span class="hebrew"> הַמְּזוּזֹת </span> <sup><b>hammezuzot</b> </sup> @Strongs.H("H4201") and on 
	the upper door post <span class="hebrew"> הַמַּשְׁקוֹף </span> <sup><b>hammashkof</b> </sup> @Strongs.H("H4947") of the houses,
	wherein they shall eat it <span class="hebrew"> אֹתוֹ </span> <sup><b>oto</b> </sup> @Strongs.H("H853").
</p>

<p class="card-text ms-4">
