	</a>
	And thou shalt write them upon the posts <span class="hebrew"> מְזוּזֹת </span> <sup><b>mezuzot</b> </sup> @Strongs.H("H4201") of thy house, and on thy gates.
</p>

<p class="card-text">
	<sup class="verse-number">8</sup> And they shall eat the flesh in that night, roast with fire, and unleavened bread;
	[and] with bitter [herbs] they shall eat it <span class="hebrew"> אֶת־ </span> <sup><b>et-</b> </sup> @Strongs.H("H853").
	
	<sup class="verse-number">9</sup> Eat not of it raw, nor sodden at all with water, but roast [with] fire;
	his head with his legs, and with the purtenance thereof.

	<sup class="verse-number">10</sup> And ye shall let nothing of it remain until the morning; and that which remaineth of it until the morning ye shall burn with fire.
</p>

